Fărâmiţă Lambru (September 15, 1927 in Bucharest – December 12, 1974,  Bucharest) was a well-known Romani lăutar from Romania.
He collaborated with Maria Tănase from 1953 until Maria Tănase died.
Between 1952 and 1956, he was an instrumentalist in the folk music ensemble of the Bucharest Estates Theater, and in 1956 he moved to the band "Constantin Tănase".

In 1967, he made his acting debut, playing in the musical "Groapa" as the singer Zavaidoc.
Between 1963-1970 he served as bandmaster, vocal and lead singer of the folk music band at the "Vasilescu" Regional Theater in Bucharest.
He took artistic tours in France (1965 and 1967), in the German Democratic Republic (1966), Italy (1966) and Moscow, U.S.S.R., gaining international fame.
